description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a highly motivated recruiter, looking for a new challenge within our friendly Recruitment team at Dorset County Hospital? We have a great opportunity for someone who wants to combine working in a dynamic fast paced recruitment environment with effective work life balance in this part time role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;work proactively as part of the Recruitment team to deliver a responsive, accurate and flexible service.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;maintain and develop our recruitment processes to ensure quality at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;promote and deliver a high quality service to all our customers including line managers, new employees and potential applicants.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualifications at GCSE level/NVQ Level 3 or equivalent in English and Maths.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recent and significant experience of working within a recruitment, employment agency or human resources environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience of working in a customer focused environment and providing support by telephone, email and face to face.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Significant experience of undertaking a range of administrative tasks and competence in Microsoft Office and web based systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a Trust that celebrates diversity and we are committed to creating an inclusive environment for all employees. We would welcome applications from people in groups which are under-represented in our organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hilary Harrold Head of Workforce Resourcing on 01305 254636 or email hilary.harrold@dchft.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
